New Records: Ben Stokes scored his first World Cup hundred
Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes put on England's third highest seventh-wicket stand in ODIs
Key Match Events: England posted a challenging total of 339/9 after opting to bat first
Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes added 129 runs for the seventh wicket
England restricted Netherlands to 179/10 to win by 160 runs
Pre-Game Insights: England captain Jos Buttler won his sixth toss in a row, opting to bat first
England made two changes, bringing in Harry Brook and Gus Atkinson for Liam Livingstone and Mark Wood
Netherlands included Teja Nidamanuru in place of Saqib Zulfiqar
Post-Match Reflections: England secured the spoils in their de facto European Cup final
England clambered three places in the tournament standings on net run-rate, from tenth to seventh
England's achievement would be small beer compared to their original tournament ambitions
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's highest stand for the seventh wicket or lower at ODI World Cups
Netherlands' tenth run-out of the tournament
England's best effort at this World Cup in the first ten overs
